This paper deals with auctions and algorithms for combinatorial allocation problems, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the social welfare and equilibrium concepts, which are relevant to the field of computational economics (cs.EC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
